news.title: Sunac China & its services unit plunge on share placement, stake sale
news.para: Sunac also sold a 5.1% stake in Sunac Services at HK$14.75 per share to raise HK$2.33 billion. The share price of Sunac Services plunged as much as 13.8% to HK$14.28.

news.title: China Aoyuan to sell assets worth $115 million
news.para: An estimated loss of around HK$177 million ($22.7 million) was expected from the disposal of shares in the small developer's units Double Bliss, Mingwan Investments and Prestige Well. The HK$900 million includes sales of shares and loans.

news.title: New home prices in China fell the most in October since February 2015
news.para: Most analysts, however, expect demand and supply to return to more normal conditions by the end of the year or early 2022 as regulators tweak their policies to stabilise the sector.

news.title: CPPIB, Phoenix Mills ink joint venture for office-led mixed-use assets development
news.para: CPPIB to invest Rs 1,350 crore to jointly develop 1 million sq ft offices, 2 lakh sq ft retail asset in Mumbai’s Lower Parel

news.title: Mumbai: Malabar Hill flat sale on slippery slope, Rs 5 crore cheating FIR filed
news.para: The FIR was filed by Malabar police on October 30 based on a complaint by Bhagwanram Bishnoi, who had wanted to buy a 1,360sq ft flat in Radha Krishna Cooperative Housing Society for Rs 10.9 crore.

news.title: Anarock looks to raise Rs 750 crore to acquire proptech startups & expand business
news.para: "We are looking to raise around USD 100 million as equity. There are many opportunities in the market for the acquisition of proptech firms. We want to acquire some of those companies, which fit in our growth strategies," said Anarock Chairman Anuj Puri.

news.title: Construction sites flout NGT norms in Lucknow
news.para: As per the NGT norms, the construction sites must control dispersion of dust into the atmosphere by covering the sites with green nets and sprinkling of water.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: Plans afoot to set up granite mining zone in Prakasam district
news.para: Setting its focus on unexplored mining areas, the state government has decided to close down the existing state highway for a distance of about 4 km near Chimakurthy in Prakasam district. This will facilitate the government to create an exclusive mining zone.

news.title: Kolkata civic body to raze illegal building extensions
news.para: The circular to executive engineers specifies the power they are bestowed with to serve notice and subsequently demolish illegal structures made by owners and developers.

news.title: Kerala: New land lease policy on anvil
news.para: The new land lease policy, while allotting government land for industrial purposes, will liberalize the conditions for entrepreneurs, allowing them to change ownership of the enterprise, change the business and it will also entail an exit policy for the entrepreneur.

news.title: WeWork opens over 15,000 sq ft workspace in Express Towers, Mumbai
news.para: The centre will have over 250 desks. In July 2021, the company had leased out 17,000 sq ft area to 3M India

news.title: Delhi: Construction ban adds to workers' unending woes
news.para: Most of the labourers live in makeshift tin sheds with piles of construction materials stacked near them. On Sunday, most workers were seen sitting and chatting on the roadside.

news.title: Thane: Forum orders housing society to pay Rs 20,000 to flat owner over car parking
news.para: The forum also directed the society to conduct a general body meeting and table a proposal for seeking approval for the complainant’s car parking on the society premises.

news.title: Redevelopment boost in Maharashtra gives Mhada record payoff
news.para: In just five months, from April to August 2021, MHADA collected Rs 1,171.86 crore through this approach. In comparison, in 12 months from April 2020 to March 2021, the agency had collected 261.38 crore.

news.title: Saya Homes to invest Rs 200 crore in new shopping mall in Noida
news.para: "We are coming up with a shopping centre in Noida. We have acquired a plot in Jaypee township," Saya Homes Managing Director Vikas Bhasin said. The project is expected to be completed in the next two years.
